In the tech industry, having a qualification is not enough – continuing professional development is key to proving that you know what you’re doing and can be trusted to provide a competitive edge. In the ever-changing world of ICT, you can’t afford to miss out on the latest trends and technology. For this reason, EE Publishers is hosting the ICT Infrastructure 2019 Conference and Exhibition taking place on 28 and 29 August at Emperors Palace, Johannesburg. Gartner predicts that in the next five years, infrastructure organisations will need to implement vastly different roles and technologies. Business leaders need to identify the skills, technologies and processes required to ensure their organisations’ continued relevance. The ICT Infrastructure 2019 Conference and Exhibition will educate delegates on various aspects involved in ensuring a world-class ICT infrastructure system for their business, with the latest updates and technology showcase covering: Click here to download the full conference programme. Click here to register. <img class="wp-image-316929 size-large aligncenter" src="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/IMG_20190722_111359-002-640x362.jpg" alt="" width="640" height="362" srcset="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/IMG_20190722_111359-002-640x362.jpg 640w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/IMG_20190722_111359-002-600x340.jpg 600w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/IMG_20190722_111359-002-768x435.jpg 768w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/IMG_20190722_111359-002-1200x679.jpg 1200w" sizes="(max-width: 709px) 85vw, (max-width: 909px) 67vw, (max-width: 984px) 61vw, (max-width: 1362px) 45vw, 600px" /> The conference has been validated by the South African Institute for Electrical Engineers (SAIEE) and qualifies for 2 CPD points in terms of the ECSA CPD scheme. Additionally, the Institute of Information Technology Professionals South Africa (IITPSA) has accredited the conference for 7 CPD points per day. Discounts on delegate fees apply for members of these institutes. In addition to tech-talks and showcases, the event features various networking opportunities and associated social engagements with leaders in the industry. For interested ICT customers who are not attending the entire conference, entry into the exhibition hall is free-of-charge (note, this means you can not get your CPD points and catering is not supplied). Download the free exhibition ticket here and bring it with you to the event. ICT infrastructure practices need to be increasingly agile to meet todays’ digital business needs. Infrastructure leaders must go far beyond being IT specialists. Today’s IT leaders need to be versatile. See technology in action and learn what it means to be versatile at ICT Infrastructure 2019, featuring a showcase of leading technology, as well as data centre site visits to Teraco’s vendor neutral data centre. Contact Charmaine Manicom, EE Publishers, Tel 011 543-7000, charmaine.manicom@ee.co.za This article was published in partnership with EE Publishers.